1 Sec. 1. Authority to convey state property. Resolved: That, notwithstanding
2 any provision of law to the contrary, the State, by and through the Commissioner of
3 Administrative and Financial Services, referred to in this resolve as "the commissioner,"
4 may convey to United Cerebral Palsy of Northeastern Maine a single-story brick building,
5 known as "the Elizabeth Levinson Center," approximately 25,412 square feet in size and
6 located at 159 Hogan Road in Bangor.
7 Sec. 2. Property to be sold "as is". Resolved: That the commissioner may
8 negotiate and execute a purchase and sale agreement for transfer of the building pursuant
9 to section 1 upon terms the commissioner considers appropriate; however, the building to
10 be sold must be transferred "as is," with no representations or warranties. The purchase
11 price of the building must be the current market value as described in section 3 but may not
12 exceed $100,000.
13 Sec. 3. Opinion of value. Resolved: That the commissioner shall have the current
14 market value of the building described in section 1 determined by a broker opinion of value
15 and current comparative market analysis.
16 Sec. 4. Proceeds. Resolved: That any proceeds from the building sale must be used
17 to reimburse the Department of Administrative and Financial Services for administrative
18 expenses and be deposited into the Bureau of General Services capital repair and
19 improvement account for capital improvements.
20 Sec. 5. Repeal. Resolved: That the authority of the commissioner to convey the
21 property described in section 1 under this resolve is repealed 5 years from its effective date.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This resolve authorizes the Department of Administrative and Financial Services to
2244 convey a building at 159 Hogan Road in Bangor, currently leased to United Cerebral Palsy
2255 of Northeastern Maine and known as "the Elizabeth Levinson Center," to United Cerebral
2266 Palsy of Northeastern Maine.
